Female refugees and their children say they're in a dire situation being moved from place to place. Courtesy #DStv403 PRETORIA - Foreign nationals in Pretoria are pleading for assistance from the UN Refugee Agency. It’s been two months since violent clashes erupted with police. Some have been released from prison while others spent Christmas without their loved ones. READ: Refugee leader arrested at Cape Town church Female refugees and their children say they're in a dire situation being moved from place to place. eNCA’s attempts to get comment from the UNHCR were unsuccessful. Editors note: The refugees' identities have been hidden for their safety.